# How to update your website
 
A plain-English guide to editing your site directly on **github.com** — no code
editor, no git, no downloads. You only ever change the words; the design takes
care of itself.
 
---
 
## The basics (read this once)
 
**How to edit any file:**
1. Go to your repo: `github.com/danielmehus/danielmehus.github.io`
2. Click the file you want to change (`index.html`, `thoughts.html`, or `projects.html`).
3. Click the **pencil icon** (✏️ "Edit this file"), top right of the file view.
4. Make your change in the text box.
5. Scroll down, click the green **"Commit changes…"** button, then **"Commit changes"** again in the popup.
6. Wait about a minute, then open your site and **hard-refresh**:
   - Windows: **Ctrl + Shift + R**
   - Mac: **Cmd + Shift + R**
That hard-refresh is important — without it your browser may keep showing the old version and you'll think nothing happened.
 
**The two things you must NOT touch:**
- Anything between `<style>` and `</style>` — that's the design. Leave it alone.
- The `<nav> … </nav>` block — that's the menu (covered at the very bottom if you ever need it).
You only edit text **between `<article class="article">` and `</article>`**. That's your content.
 
**Tip:** to find text fast while editing, press **Ctrl + F** (Mac: **Cmd + F**) and type a few words you can see on the page.
 
