## 1. The About page (`index.html`)
 
This is your homepage. Find this block:
 
```html
<h1>Daniel Mehus</h1>
 
<p>Write a brief introduction about yourself here. ...</p>
 
<p>Add more context about your background ...</p>
 
<p>You can gain further insights ... find me on
  <a href="https://github.com/" ...>GitHub</a>,
  <a href="https://x.com/" ...>X/Twitter</a>, and
  <a href="https://linkedin.com/" ...>LinkedIn</a>.</p>
```
 
**Change your name:** edit the words between `<h1>` and `</h1>`.
 
**Change the intro:** replace the text inside each `<p> … </p>`. Keep the `<p>` and `</p>` tags — just swap the words between them.
 
**Fix your social links:** put your real URLs inside the quotes. For example:
 
```html
<a href="https://github.com/danielmehus" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">GitHub</a>
```
 
Only change the part inside the quotes (`https://github.com/danielmehus`) and the word between `>` and `</a>` (`GitHub`). Leave the rest as-is.
 
