## 3. The Projects page (`projects.html`)
 
Each project is a heading plus a paragraph:
 
```html
<h2 class="section" id="project-one">
  <a class="anchor" href="#project-one" aria-label="Link to this section">#</a>
  <a href="https://example.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Project One</a>
</h2>
<p>Describe the project: what it is, when you made it, your role ...</p>
```
 
**To edit a project:**
- Change `Project One` (the text between `>` and `</a>` on the second link) → the project's name.
- Change `https://example.com` (the second link's `href`) → where the project lives.
- Change the text inside `<p> … </p>` → the description.
**The `id` (one rule):** each `<h2>` has an `id="project-one"`. The `#` link just above it must use the **same** word with a `#` in front (`href="#project-one"`). If you add a new project, give it a unique id (e.g. `id="project-four"` and `href="#project-four"`). If that feels fiddly, you can ignore the `#` link — it only adds a little hover anchor and the page works fine without worrying about it.
 
**To add a project:** copy a full `<h2 …> … </h2>` block **and** the `<p> … </p>` right after it, paste below, and edit the three things above (plus the id if you want the anchor to work).
 
**The lists at the bottom** ("Smaller experiments") work like the Thoughts list — copy a `<li> … </li>` to add a row:
 
```html
<li><a href="https://example.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Experiment A</a></li>
```
 
Change the URL in the quotes and the name between `>` and `</a>`.
 
**To remove a section divider** (the short horizontal line), delete a line that says `<hr />`. To keep it, leave it.
 
